            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1634032064194-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the noodles are cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once the pan is hot, drain, then add your <strong>king</strong> <strong>prawns</strong> with your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> and cook for 4-5 min until cooked through</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634032069140-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634032069140-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634032069140-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634032069140-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634032069140-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>mangetout</strong> in half roughly (chop them in one bunch for speed)</p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Once the noodles are almost cooked, add the <strong>halved mangetout</strong> and cook for 1 min or until just cooked with a bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain the <strong>noodles & mangetout </strong>and reserve a cup of the<strong> starchy noodle water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
